I used a tinned steel pan which made beautiful golden brown Madeleines. After reading the reviews, I tried several variations. I melted a little extra butter and buttered the indentations in the pan with a pastry brush. Dusting with flour does, indeed, make them easier to remove and waiting 5 minutes before taking them out of the pan keeps them from looking mottled (if you take them out sooner, the butter/flour sticks to them). I didn't find that putting the pans in the freezer made a difference. I've had good results making the batter a day ahead (as some suggest) and good results using it immediately. Ive made them with 10 T butter and 8 T of butter and preferred the lighter ones. VERY easy to make and very enthusiastically received. Definitely worth investing in a tinned steel pan. (I bought mine on amazon for $12.)

