I just want to add a note as the reviewer before me disagreed with the cooking time, amount, etc. I, however, did bake them in the middle of my oven for @15minutes and put @one tablespoon batter in each mold, and they turned out great. Maybe she/he needs to readjust their oven?

Rating: 2
The recipe is not very precise. It should be baked in the lower third of the oven, which wasn't specified. And it's enough to spray the pan with an oil spray, no need for the flour(if a non stick pan is used). A whole tablespoon is too much batter for one mold,(the larger mold)--one teaspoon is enough,or even less. The time is too much as well,10 min is plenty or untill edges are slightly golden. The cakes came out too dry and not very fluffy. But its edible.